separate times for different projects.  I worked with Adam and Dominique on my upper deck project and again years later for my Bath House rebuild due to storm damage.  I would not hesitate to hire them again to replace my flat roof with IB.  Both Adam and Dominique have the knowledge and experience to get the job done with quality results.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Liz McClure","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6cBz7q7b_97NEfKJrE6rORiCb4JQBUOryRmq3QLbzyRdskxMw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Owner Adam made a thorough inspection of our third story condo building roof as we made plans for a PVC overlay. His competitive bid reflected LifeTime’s commitment to quality work at a fair price. Communication throughout our project was clear and informative. The crew was great, working efficiently while maintaining attention to detail. I highly recommend LifeTime for its deep track record of quality roofing and for working with our HOA start to finish.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aldo Basile","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1Oz9zjbAAzXm17j3PaUP76B6bnYiqZn_k4q-akKNGCxJNdJ77=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had contacted Adam, the company owner, to assess our roof conditions. Adam was very thorough when inspecting the roof, providing a fair assessment of what needed to be done. We analyzed several bids by other companies and decided to pursue a roof replacement with Lifetime Flat Roofs after several conversations with Adam, who was always ready to provide explanations and suggestions on the project.\nThe crew charged with the roof replacement did a great job with showing on time, respectful of the property and the neighborhood, and staying on the task until completion. We were kept informed about progress at all times by the foreman, Alec.\nThe positive experience was also enhanced by the contacts with the officer manager, Katy, who kept us abreast of the timing of the project and handled the administrative side after completion.\nAll in all we have had a positive experience with Lifetime and the roof replacement process. Of course, we will be even more pleased once we pass the rain test after our dry and hot summer! Yes, we definitely would recommend Lifetime.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Spade Jac","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUz3kWjfxBq64HTuWghDJZ6_JHppEg-w5X8sRZXzwGV1gaKuQkuxA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Would not recommend. Your neighbors would hate you for hiring these guys. Fully blocked my driveway for hours out and was using my driveway as a work area while working on my neighbors house, none of which I had a problem with because people need to get stuff done.\n\nLater they parked another long work van in a non-parking spot partially blocking my driveway. When approached to ask not to do that in the future, because it created a road hazard from blocking out view to the traffic for me, got a rude unprofessional response telling me there was enough space for me to get out if I needed.\n\nAll of this while there was ample parking available in the neighborhood including on the opposite side of the street. Professionalism is not their strong suit.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn15zipuRW_GGusqqtrLq5QnrdcKY7iY0OEOgfrZJCACYMgsMgWD3eEE4RAwzhuzZ-3zT4P2O9dxDgM82cGYNeyYLNEIYnnS_OEw9z2nFg7amS9YmayCh0z8A3d8azc2nbKgoiE=k-no"],"When":"2023-6-5"},{"Name":"D Beisel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKhboLpFotCrBAfDFIrE26wPLXoqKi_Uyd-aXwq3M8OAzpqQw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a slow leak in the valley that caused rot on our low-sloped roof that showed up as a leak in our ceiling. The company that originally installed the roof about 15 years ago came out to inspect it and all they did was confirm there was a leak but did nothing in terms of follow-up for repair.\n\nMy neighbor had Lifetime do his roof and recommended them for their good work and competitive pricing. Adam was great all the way through in terms of scheduling, follow-up, explaining the process and estimates and costs.\n\nSam came out to investigate the issue and did a thorough job figuring out what was causing the leak and offered repair solutions. He brought me up to the roof to show me other areas with potential issues due to poor original installation. Seams were coming up, there were soft spots due to improper sheathing installation, etc. He even did temporary repairs on the spot and I never got charged for his time.\n\nI decided that after talking with Adam, it was best to go ahead and get a new roof installed. He even knocked some $ off the estimate in order for me to accept it. We agreed that anything additional to the estimate like sheathing repair would be charged at time and wholesale cost of materials. Adam updated me on a nearly daily basis the cost of the extras. The final invoice reflected what was agreed upon and was completely fair.\n\nChris and his team worked as hard as any group of workers I've seen. They showed up everyday they said they would and on time or EARLY!! Chris was very communicative and explained everything they were doing and took me up to the roof as well. We talked every morning when they arrived and every night before they left. They put in a few 12 hour days to get the job done in a timely manner. The crew worked well together, they were proficient and courteous. They did a beautiful job and cleaned up thoroughly at the end of each day.\n\nIf you need a new low-sloped or flat roof, these are the guys to go to!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Helen SSF","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJdIjLvwofOWn3cOkrq-wriyME9SeonJ6WSTmfUAVA_OqPNGw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would highly recommend Lifetime Flat roofs as they really put the customer needs as their top priority and tried to solve the customer's problem timely and efficiently.\n\nLifetime Flat Roofs did a terrific job repairing my PVC roof. I had leaks in the PVC area of my roof. My friend referred Lifetime Flat Roofs to me. Adam stopped by soon, did a thorough examination of the roof and found the problematic areas. When he knew that I really need it fixed before the rainy weekend, he went extra miles to arrange a repair for me the next day. Otherwise, we could have waited another rainy week to get it repaired. We have contacted many other roofers but none was like Lifetime Flat roofs that really tried to solve the customer's problem timely. We deeply appreciate that.\n\nThe work crew was professional and did a wonderful job. Very easy to communicate with the crew. Even if I asked them to check or seal additional areas, they were always willing to help. They were also very responsible and reliable. Before I have the drywall patched up, they kindly stopped by to double check and make sure no more leaks before patching up the drywall. This means a lot to us and made us feel so safe and worry-free working with them.  A big thumb up.\n\nWe were very pleased working with Lifetime Flat roofs and highly recommend them for your roof needs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeanna Hammar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_HDFHg4iNEs0cYl8CiMcYLmlakHVyRIZW96SAbQpwH4AbiV0EKw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Highly recommend. They have a great product + warranty, professional staff \u0026 quick turn-around\n\nWe had a leaking flat roof deck, so they sent a consultant out to view the roof within the week \u0026 issued a prompt quote within a few days\n\nThe job was scheduled within the month and rain delayed the job by one day. The crew was large and they all worked well together. The entire roof was ripped off \u0026 fully replaced in one day and minimal roof rot was replaced as they went. They worked over twelve hours getting it all done \u0026 made sure everything was sealed up nicely before they left\n\nBefore they left, they proactively did a quick inspection of one of the other roofs and noted a few issues with it that could lead to premature failure; this was so nice of them!\n\nGreat communication from start to finish with all of our questions \u0026 concerns -- they even took calls late on Friday evening for our early Monday start date","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
