oung son and one on the way, we needed a tub to replace the shower as no bathroom in the house has a tub. Jose took our designer's plans and we worked with him to make it executable. We were responsible for buying all finish materials and had them ready for him on just about day one. His crew set out flooring protection and wall protection to keep as much dust contained as possible. Jose and his team, who were fantastic, accommodated our desire to remove and blow back in nearly new insulation in our attic to raise the ceilings to match the rest of the house. They laid large format tile on the floor and executed a ¼ offset tub surround tile, while adding beautiful vertical blue tile behind a floating vanity. Tile really was the standout part of this project and Jose nailed it with flush, flat, surfaces on three different tiles. The shower niche is a lowkey highlight as the way Jose was able to cut the tile reduced grout lines and he even set the shelves at a slight angle to let water drip out.\n\nThe project turned out amazing, and Jose's attention to detail was great; he hit is completiondate to the day. I expected to have a long punch list as I'm quite detail oriented myself, but it was surprisingly short with all the finishing touches, sealants, straight paint lines, and care with the finish materials. I would 100% work with Jose again and look forward to our next project together.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn16GUHlS9h7TFpR0DF8bfaTdYxkGedli-mkq4ZIL14yC8dtoQD7kdkgvlnlSLh1LYlJm6hEQtIr7RBirKS09Oprw7k8yO7jsF00x04g-SPrhzF5Q3L1Mc3jQYUb1-nFGVWvWY35=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0b4nRvdnYmzbRyXKQgccjCL16Yzzva4-kgcUiXcxYL5Q32vieFxzbnUdClX_5uvl1UMQ4fYxVnUtHUaamSdCWt9xJS6MZTwlI4R5S6NgL14QyRAj3szBJfWA38_j4hJqi0Skxq=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2ISS-LJ8p6triLCcxICuLc1rRNxafTVQD7MMTipwn3dsIz_pb4BQMALy0b0fe-oWKcgWU61OXlRK5T8xVpsKtm653bwgPk8iMtKzIHypEA5_ZrI59FF-hisGbr_pSdejD4X18=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1aZKopEdotnv6vXS29rqH3GcUtijrZQwD5yCPc6xWNkhwWiDoEbNZTALgvTzP3-hadF1fFS3ArZrPkJ4oeHTZM1jsI2MTO7-ZNwYgV6UWPJInwzvp7Zlz_v0BRQOy-_K65_hPADg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0kiMoSNkLT0NUTdqpW3ruoT0znASwiAe14zIp21syp9czwrLwdo9JUeIvMM8a-Z0yf6lx-ptMHiE1Rnp_vjBdcvSCvcpBLgZRQPbyKy-2jes-TA8FxHBxbwsgF3K_2RLBQHJsF=k-no"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"Angelina Vasquez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLx3uEqdbiSV4jWAmE5rIM65futSlnKMZHAvILdgx0JsDX9ZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I cannot give enough praise to Jose and his team at Cruz construction. I reached out to him in late August to get a bid for a full bathroom remodel. He responded quickly and was out to give us an estimate within a few days.\nI was amazed at not only his professionalism, but how easy he was to talk to about the project. He listened to my ideas, and presented a beautiful design.\nFrom the time we agreed to the project, he was in continual communication with us. We were able to fully start the remodel in January, but even before then, he assisted us with picking out materials, helping us choose items from from different vendors, and working out details that we had thought of. Unlike other contractors, very small details matter to him. He is attentive to the most minor inaccuracies, and will go back and correct them until he and I are both happy.\nIn the past, we’ve had difficulties not having a project manager onsite. Not the case with Cruz Construction. Jose was here almost daily (M-F), unless he was picking up materials, which was always communicated to us. We also appreciated the additional security provided by having a lock box for the key to our house. He didn’t even seem to be bothered by our dogs, who were kenneled, but can be very vocal.\nJose gave us a dream bathroom, down to the detailing on the shampoo shelves. I would totally work with him again on future projects, and will be doing so for my daughter’s bathroom in the near future.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3kpWAX9AfPd-MwpfuJIiEMkWPTlCjcJp0SNS0UdUvT5QHilXL9IXeAdPxIvkmRK8sal-mOQFtDThUk7blCZ-AOnArrM_c4LcWZXGLbhkMuk-HnJ8BGSZtUwrtrNj7Y55hd77D0=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1lGhNkfihWuT33-PV5K1D1fgprgKGDzGpY2dxGPirV0oVN0ozXPg4d5ijkJsW3ssQOv3EtKqVbBzwZ-Td_e0P5B8RR5lab3looz4ceHG8YaVZd3ygmfsgRmQly22qJWQ3EggqJZg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1_uqLykXAd4VV1C7WvpMfEYGivFDj04GOjW2nXSagxOjNL97zQ1onCBwFDYC9QQthKpDW96NxUPyE2FotrxSN97Y5e1cFe7VxHQ-vnVapFzwpXNCjwkvdd1KWtrIPRGszfGHhg=k-no"],"When":"2024-3-2"}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
