ust honest advice.\n\nJuan and Mario showed up on time and worked super efficiently. In about three hours, they got everything done perfectly, roof and gutters cleaned, gutters fixed, everything spotless. I really appreciated their work ethic and the way they went above and beyond without me even asking. They cleaned the small shed roof that isn't connected to the house, adjusted other parts of the gutter that needed attention, and left the whole place so clean. Not just the debris from the roof and gutter, they even blew away the storm branches and leaves around the yard.\n\nHonestly, driving home and seeing how clean and fresh everything looked made me so happy. I highly recommend All Access Roofing \u0026 Gutters, and especially Juan, Mario, and Yolanda. If you want honest people who do excellent work, these are your guys.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kevin Todd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwBD9aKRJEANfLlDXFJL-CWTZdaiaJV6c5UVGSgwF-J_QGPIo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our 34-year-old gutters were done, and we contacted All Access Roofing \u0026 Gutters for help.  Within hours, Pascal reached out and we set up a free estimate appt for 9/28.  The price was fair, he added a free moss roof treatment, and we booked a gutter/downspout replacement for 10/3.  On the day of, Juan and his crew arrived and went straight to work.  No lie, I watched in the beginning.  Impressive work ethic, great attention to detail and workmanship, I felt good about these guys.  By the late afternoon, it was done.  Their clean-up was excellent, Juan explained a few minor changes he made to help with water flow, and said to contact him for any issues.  On the morning of 10/4, it rained and you bet I was outside checking it all out.\n\nIt was all good, such a nice feeling.  Thanks to Pascal, Juan, his crew for doing a solid job.  I appreciate quality work, done well.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0MQ-aBX