killfully caulked and replaced the flashing, ensuring a leak-proof finish. He also maintained cleanliness at the site after finishing the job.\nOverall, I am extremely satisfied with the service quality and the outcome.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2u9TFx21LbjI6tPb_bqP--CidTGUOs11knaJBKTx0pmffVHbqmOJelf14nqQCM98rL0z_0SdfOO2PKhVXkNlNEcMguq8nqdjUQKc5nkxkKFoT8ibCrICG89kfY5JPux7uj2D1IUg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3xLhrtUXjOqk_TShyp_zjX2yAyVL-t4NY30K9GOOOJFmoVeGnEk0vQ2sGWQOnM7EZOgqoItUEjGqwvAp31WK5czNfRULQ_GesTdBQqHbw1bZIL182ewbg8VA-1P7sC3t-15iM=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn320Z0R2JaML6CHMsrE622qopX-gUmrK8KSd0pUcbyZbkPMgk5J3RhPqO_KU5a6o-fVvVTc7-3jFaHEWe5YO6gtS-hppphSIHac1_6gwYIBlbyKm7IziaieboBsecwVngrno-gTVw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2KsODBJ-pw984wNbpE4ietzbQL-iiEhNQJYWn6E8i33sh7g8b08-LD9njeajR7YrQhvGu8n7h4J82ehm4FT5jmd3YrjK3GcYOCISv9X08ljA4FKXJ-tAFvCqopam66JQyKiv8=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn33RFrzP4H4crw-K1HEmkQE4Clae6pA3PFOjdfrQasX4OAuC3tWXxdP6Srj306JqjAHXYXOUNhZEBu4dMEy8xUh4alADxucGjqtfTtlog3-pUbCsrp3Jm0LpOvTR-0yUNN9ECx3=k-no"],"When":"2024-2-2"},{"Name":"Oziel Arjona","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK43de42SKE7vcSt5CXsUvuBLlZTEQxSsbozmyPAFGCMmMUjw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would like to say Fidel and his crew did a phenomenal job on multiple projects around the house. I requested the kitchen floors be replaced, front porch exterior planks be refurbished and replace the rotted ones, touch up paint in the bathroom downstairs, refurnish multiple wooden sills(dogs nails scraped the wood), pressure wash the house, patio tile the back steps, and replace the vanity to the upstairs bathroom with one I just purchased from home depot.  I never felt pressured to do anything and if there were any hiccups Fidel would advise me of them and  provide solutions.\n\nFor example my old vanity had a vent and it was bigger than the new one I purchased. Fidel was able to cut into the new vanity and place it on the side (the front had a gap in the front where the vent would have gone). Also the old backsplash left residue on the wall that extended further than the new vanity. He asked if I had paint for the bathroom which I did and he painted it. He did all of this with no extra charge. Unlike my previous general contractors who would state that’s not exactly what you paid me to do, versus he finishes the job on the intent of the work.\n\nI had old contractors who would say they could do something but it felt like they were just trying to figure it out as they go. Fidel was able to do most of the projects but would bring in additional workers to help finish the projects. All the additional workers worked diligently and were professional.\n\nThe materials he provide for the floors were better quality than the ones I had chosen (same pattern and color) or what came with the house.\n\nI added some photos (the step design is what I wanted but I’m sure if you wanted a different design their team could do it)\n\nAs a first responder I am impressed with him and his team. I would definitely recommend this company to others who want quality work for a great price, and not have to fear they would be nickel and dime extra money through their projects, or the fear a company stop showing up half way through a project.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1r0Fdo8K10QITxdSAQ9hcoWIm0-cz3gBMM4xoL9Xgtcl_TJoEe03YSxqOoI0boxSJBZBpZUN0A7HLyu0cfHptV-2YklENWtgqIMeca0eCMrfG5SDpIcn3f_rP3YhhfPA7nPiw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3XeM-s2ShiQv-DTkp5dNWzK2-YQWWHaScSmLvFsWhkPL16lxu-2Xsxp0waSK59zRB6nAL7ju7OSUAY8MtpwjDawj_8CSZBzGOH31to_cqVmbHcSPZ46zwyYaSy44xRIxvYmcs1=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1i470T1s9kpgfuOgfvyujeO7fDXXsdnPn_OZIQTrYIG6HuwfBMRPtuB0KWJ6L0hEWAQI00oopUwkxy_KQeXQdPxvyBodyjKwnA5A_jfxOG2TwRsZK6jcYdkt